==English==

===Etymology===
From The Bible account of Jesus' last night in Gethsemane. [[s:Bible (King James)/Matthew#Chapter 26|Matthew Ch.26:41]]. ''Watch and pray, that ye enter not into temptation: the spirit indeed is willing, but the flesh is weak.''

===Proverb===
'''the [[spirit]] is [[willing]] but the [[flesh]] is [[weak]]'''

# (proverbs) For much as one wishes to [[achieve]] something, the [[frailty|frailties]] of the human body often make it [[impossible]].

